<br>
Let's take a look at exp gains:<br>
<br>
You could get 1AA every 4hrs soloing in FG (pre PoP). zero risk.<br>
<br>
1 AA every 2hrs in a full PoValor group, very low risk.<br>
1 AA every 1.5hrs in a full Halls of Honor group, low risk and chance to get spectrals.<br>
<br>
1 AA every 1hr soloing (with cleric bot, so more like duoing) in BoT, high risk - rare dropping eth/spec - very rare (rare named drop) rune.<br>
<br>
I haven't tried to exp in elemental planes yet, but based on the raid exp I think 1 AA every 45min or so in a full group at mid risk is doable. Not to mention tradeskill components for some really nice items. also spec/runes of course. (not sure if random mobs also have a chance to drop any ornate/elemental armor?)<br>
--<br>
<br>
The higher you move up in tiers, the higher the risk and the better the exp. <br>
<br>
To get this 1AA/hr soloing in BoT you need more than average gear and a lvl 65 spell. (which is our only real useful one btw, Vortex isnt a huge upgrade to ancient/black steel and earth pet is weaker than air in most situations)<br>
<br>
Chanters have it easier to charm kill than mages - no question, but it has been one of there class abilities since release. <br>
<br>
If you want to see how it is to charm hunt go to valor and try to channel a malosinia through 2 mobs meleeing you. (the charmed pet + the mob you were fighting) <br>
Considering its a lvl 65 spell it will be harder to channel and it has a few seconds recast time so you dont want it to get resisted. (the mob you're fighting will most likely summon you so staying far enough away isnt going to help much =/)<br>
<br>
Now (for max exp gain) imagine this with one of them having 85% haste. (and add flurry/rampage to it if you use FB)<br>
<br>
