 Wagon&quot; here...<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>First:</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Death IS in fact a factor since it adds a LOT of time to the process.<br>
<br>
Unless the Enchanter has a support crew of high level Druids, Beastlords, Clerics and Shamans standing by to buff/Rez them for free every time they die, there is a huge time sink in getting the buffs back that you lose when dying. (Normally 15-25 minutes.)<br>
<br>
Then there's load times, zoning times and self buffing/mana regen from self buffing times. (Add in 10-15 minutes to complete this process.)<br>
<br>
For those that think Enchanters can just gate out to recoup their resources.. they can't heal themselves. There is a lot of downtime when your runes don't hold stuff back and you take damage...<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Second:</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
If you scale down the damage output and overall power of the Charmed mobs, then scale UP the reliability of the Charm spells themselves and reduce the mana cost to make it more effective. Even with ALL the AA's that make Charming easier it's still VERY unreliable and with Total Domination 3 you can have charm break the INSTANT you cast it.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Finally:</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
If you think it’s a particular encounter that’s the problem. (I’ve heard the word exploit used here so it must be involving a few limited locations in some part.)<br>
<br>
Here’s the solution: (This is where the “Productivity Wagon” really takes off.)<br>
<br>
In Bastion of Thunder it was mentioned that an Enchanter used Invis to get to the Boss mob, Pacify to Single pull them and an easy access portal to escape death.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>1:</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Place a few see invis mobs along the path.<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>2:</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Tune Pacify versus Boss Mob Guards.<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>3:</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Make the portal require “No Aggro” to be able to use it. (This would respond much like the Tribunal when there’s a Trial in progress.. it would say “You cannot use this portal now, you have guests.”) Forcing you to CLEAR the room before using the portal.<br>
<br>
Your words would be FAR more credible if you offered this kind of thought rather than just say “It’s over powered, nerf it”<br>
<br>
P.S.<br>
I have MANY Mage friends that solo in Planes of Power. (I have more Mage friends than Chanter friends that solo in PoP anyway. In fact, I have more Druid and Wizard friends that solo in PoP than I do Enchanter friends that do it.)<br>
<br>
If YOU can’t solo in PoP as a Mage, that doesn’t mean Mages can’t do it. This argument goes both ways. You are acting as if Enchanters are running rampant soloing Gods left and right, but Mages can’t do it at all. Neither of those statements are true.<br>
